\f0\b\fs48 \cf0 INTRO
\b0\fs22 \
\
I currently work as a Senior Design & Technology Fellow at the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau, a federal agency that was established as part of the 2011 financial reform act Dodd-Frank, as envisioned by now-Senator Elizabeth Warren. The CFPB was brought into not only to act as a new banking regulator, but also to advocate for and educate American consumers. As a new agency, the CFPB wanted to break the reliance upon pricey government contracts to develop technology and opted to build out the largest team of in-house technologists and designers. \
\
I'm not here to speak on CFPB's behalf, but I did want to share a few snapshots of what we're working on. I'm currently working on a mapping tool that helps our bank investigators determine if institutions are discriminating in their lending practices based on factors like race or gender... Essentially sussing out modern day cases of redlining, also known as "disparate impact".\
\
So, I\'92m here to talk to you today about the concept of data visualization. Any regular readers of major news publications may notice an increasing trend in the use of visual depictions of data in support of the articles and breaking stories. We see them in annual reports, dashboard and analytics displays, on our apps.\
